<br>
Our petition was <b>not</b> shot down; it accomplished what it was meant to do.<br>
<br>
Not only did we get ourselves heard, but Alan also released a statement about petitions in general, which happened after our petition (among others), and GU Comics made at least two comics regarding us, our current state, and petitions. VI reads GU Comics too, you know. Don't you think Woody has given us a lot of ink time recently? If you don't think so, go check the GU Comics archives!<br>
<br>
Furthermore, on the issue of petitions, if you read what Alan preferred (he was actually trying to help), then I hope you sent in <b>your individual bullet list</b> -- I know I have for myself, and Sobe did on behalf of The Druids Grove.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<i>Druids ARE already uber. We don't need more petitions to allow the 'farming' types to get it easier to continue farming and make the 'REAL' Druids reconsider their class.</i><br>
<br>
Oh give me a break. Farming types are soloers for the most part and do their business away from raids. None of the healing changes we asked for would help farmers.<br>
<br>
<br>
<i>Think about this: What would make you a better player? More skills? Or a reduction of them?</i><br>
<br>
Duh? <b>Having more AA skills has made me a better player</b>, so I can safely choose more skills and more options over a reduction (or nerfage) of them. Even if our new skills aren't the best in the world, it certainly does make a difference in the long run and in groups -- think about it for a moment. Mana savings, extra damage, exodus, dire charm, and more. <br>
